Author: Sunopsis Version: 4.0 Last Update: DEC-2004
Description: - Loading Knowledge Module - Loads data from a Microsoft SQL Server to a Microsoft SQL Server database using Linked Servers mechanism. - A view is created on the source server and a view referencing this view is created on the target server. - When using this module on a journalized source table, the Journaling table is first updated to flag the records consumed and then cleaned from these records at the end of the interface.
Restrictions: - Supported on Microsoft SQL Server 2000 Service Pack 1. - Sunopsis user must have db_owner and db_ddladmin roles. - For automatic link server creation, Sunopsis user must have sysadmin privileges. - MSDTC Service must be started on both SQL Server instances (source and target). Make sure that : - the 'Log On As' account for the MSDTC Service is a Network Service account (and not the 'LocalSystem' account) - MSDTC is disabled for network transactions - Windows Firewall is enabled on the computer (by default, Windows Firewall blocks the MSDTC program) - you bring Microsoft SQL Server online only after MSDTC was fully up and running Use the links below for MSDTC Service troubleshootings: http://support.microsoft.com/?kbid=816701 http://support.microsoft.com/?kbid=839279

Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (tables, files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.
NB : Linked Server is managed by the AUTO_CREATE_LINKED_SERVER option in order to avoid an unexpected deletion
Create a linked server on target.
Check this option if you wish to create a linked server on the target Microsoft SQL Server.

<% if ("C".equals(snpRef.getJrnInfo( "JRN_METHOD"))) { %> /* Consistant journalization detected. */ /* Lock should be done by a specific step in a package */ <% } else { %> update <%=snpRef.getTable( "L" , "JRN_NAME" , "A" )%> set JRN_CONSUMED = '1' where (1=1) <%=snpRef.getJrnFilter()%> <% } %>

create view <%=snpRef.getInfo("SRC_WORK_SCHEMA")%>.<?=snpRef.getInfo("SRC_DSERV_NAME").replace('\','_')?><%=snpRef.getTargetTable("RES_NAME")%> as select <%=snpRef.getPop("DISTINCT_ROWS")%> <%=snpRef.getColList("", "[EXPRESSION]\t[ALIAS_SEP] [CX_COL_NAME]", ",\n\t", "", "")%> from <%=snpRef.getFrom()%> where (1=1) <%=snpRef.getFilter()%> <%=snpRef.getJrnFilter()%> <%=snpRef.getJoin()%> <%=snpRef.getGrpBy()%> <%=snpRef.getHaving()%>
Grant SELECT on view on source

create view <%=snpRef.getInfo("DEST_WORK_SCHEMA")%>.<%=snpRef.getInfo(" COLL_NAME")%> as select * from [<%=snpRef.getInfo("SRC_DSERV_NAME")%>].<%=snpRef.getInfo("SRC_WORK_CATALOG")%>.<%=snpRef.getInfo("SRC_WORK_SCHEMA")%>.<?=snpRef.getInfo("SRC_DSERV_NAME").replace('\','_')?><%=snpRef.getTargetTable("RES_NAME")%>

<% if ("C".equals(snpRef.getJrnInfo( "JRN_METHOD"))) { %> /* Consistant journalization detected. */ /* Lock should be done by a specific step in a package */ <% } else { %> delete from <%=snpRef.getTable( "L" , "JRN_NAME" , "A" )%> where JRN_CONSUMED = '1' <%=snpRef.getJrnFilter()%> <% } %>
